result.execSummary:
The defendant Porscha A. Rizzi was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 1st-Degree Intentional Homicide [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit], a class B felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.01(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and Substance Abuse Program. Defendant granted credit for 340 days served.

superMiscConds.notes:
Defendant is ordered to pay the DNA surcharge, and to make arrangements to provide a DNA sample for testing through the Clark County Sheriff Department or if on probation, to the Department of Corrections as is required in all criminal convictions.  
Fine and/or costs to be paid on a schedule established by the agent.
Defendant is to remain employed or to be in school or a combination of the two.

Defendant shall have a Mental Health Evaluation and then shall attend counseling, treatments, programming, evaluations as deemed appropriate by the agent releasing all records to the agent upon request.

Defendant is to complete all program required by the agent.

Defendant shall not possess or consume any medication or drug except as may be specifically prescribed by a medical professional for defendant, and then shall be taken only as prescribed.  

The defendant shall have no contact with William Zinser, William Mormann, Alison Keeling, Logan Keeling, Mark Weberr, Shari Klimmer, Jeffrey Jankovic, Joy Bergstrom  of any kind, whether direct or indirect, including in person, in writing, by phone, by e-mail or other electronic means, through a third party or in any other way.

Contact with P.M and T.Z. the defendant's children, to occur only pursuant to a Family Court order with the discretion/agreement of the agent.

supervisions.notes:
The defendant shall pay Department of Correction fees as directed by the agent. 
Case 15CF77, 940.48(1) Violate Order/Intimidate Witness-Force was dismissed and read-in to this case.
